Alleged Parliament arsonist Zandile Mafe is facing multiple charges, including arson and terrorism. eNCA'sAyesha Ismail has the details. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Lawyers will bring an urgent application on Saturday for alleged Parliament arsonist Zandile Mafe, to be released on bail. Mafe has been referred to the Valkenberg psychiatric hospital for mental observation after a district surgeon found he was suffering from paranoid schizophrenia. The 49-year-old is facing multiple charges, including arson and terrorism. eNCA'sAyesha Ismail has the details in the video above.